content.detailedDescription: One summer night my daughter and i put chairs in our horse pasture to listen for the mountain lion we often see and hear. the chairs were reclined so we could see the stars when we see 3 rounded shapes above trees pretty high up that seemed to be lit up. it was hard to tell if the lights were apart or continuous. they moved left to right very slowly keeping in perfect distance from each other. then stood still and moved to left then back to right and took off. we both felt it was super odd and only thought it could be a satellite but truly it was odd. can satellites move l like that. we would love to know what we truly saw. this is an extremely rural and mountainous area and there was nothing but and apple orchard behind us.
content.summary: My daughter were listening for mountain lion and looking at stars when we saw 3 rounded sets of light moving left to rt. that paused moved left hovered then moved right super fast then we're gone. we were shocked as an airplane can't move or look that way

content.detailedDescription: I was walking from my house to the store, which is only a block away right before 7pm on 1/07/2016.  i heard the sound of a helicopter, so i tried to locate it and that's when i saw this extremely bright light in front of this dark colored helicopter.  my first impression, was that it was the spot light on the helicopter, but then i realized it was roughly 100ft or so infront of the helicopter.  when i began to focus on the light, i could make out, that it was actually 3 smaller lights in a triangular formation, 2 lights on the bottom, 1 on top.  the total size of this object, to my eye, was smaller than the helicopter itself, based off of the distance between the lights on the helicopter.  both continued in a westerly direction with the helicopter maintaining around a 100ft or more distance from this object.  it made no noise, the only sound was from the helicopter.  as i watched, it crossed behind a church, so i ran to get another look and this is when, the lights slowly began to dim over a 10-15 second period, to a very dim reddish color.  all the while maintaining course until it completely disappeared.  the helicopter did not change course.  i stood in the parking lot until i lost visual of them both behind the houses and trees next to the parking lot i was in.  my initial feeling was a slight anxiety, as if it knew i was watching it, and that is why the lights dissappeared.  this only happened around 30-45 minutes ago and i'm still processing it.  it just doesn't seem right, there were no flashing lights, similar to any airplane or helicopter on the wings or tails and it was far too close to the helicopter and within a relatively close distance to the ground, where anyone could make out the sound of more than 1 aircraft.
content.summary: Ufo followed closely by dark colored helicopter

content.detailedDescription: My teenage daughter and i were driving home at 8:20pm on january 4, 2016. a clear night with a partial moon and stars in the sky.   after turning a corner, we observed a bright orb hovering in the sky ahead of us -- probably a mile or so away and not very high in the sky.  my daughter and i first thought it was a news helicopter or similar as it was close to the turnpike -- perhaps covering an accident.  however, the light/orb seemed too big for that.  the orb "drifted" slightly to the east, still appearing to be hovering.  at this point, we thought it may be the helicopter of a family that lives in that area.  after observing the hovering orb for ~30 seconds, the single large orb "turned into" 3 smaller orbs forming the shape of a triangle, with a single small red light emitting from the center of the triangle.  the triangle moved towards our location.  at this point we thought it might be a drone.  as we turned left into our neighborhood, the triangle moved parallel to us, almost directly above us.  although it was night, both my daughter and i could make out the silhouette of the object between the three lights.  i immediately said "it looks like the stealth bomber!"  we were both in awe!  within a few seconds, the triangle went from an observable object right above us to three lights disappearing on the horizon. amazing!
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path then hovering
content.summary: 1 stationary bright white orb that turned into 3 smaller white orbs in triangle shape with 1 smaller red light.  from underneath object looked similar to b2 bomber.

content.detailedDescription:
On tuesday, dec. 29, 2015 while on vacation in the davis mountains region of texas, we had to drive from ft. davis to alpine to get a new tire.  once completed we decided we'd just drive over to marfa, tx to see what was there and then make the loop back to ft. davis.  this was somewhere around 10-11am cst.  on that drive west from alpine to marfa, at about 10 miles from marfa, my wife and i noticed a white rectangular or perhaps trapezoidal shape in the distance to the west.  i first thought we were seeing something reflecting off the distant mountains, but as we got closer it was apparent it was up in the sky.  it appeared to just be up there.  as we were driving, i could not tell that it was moving at all.  just hung there in the distance.  my wife thought it must be a weather balloon, but i said it was too rectangular for that and it didn't appear to move up or down.  it was just a very odd sight.  and i have to admit, being in the area of the famous marfa lights didn't help any.  

as we got closer to marfa, we realized it was beyond the town to the west and still appeared to be almost the same size as when we'd first observed.  to do that, it must have been very large.  we lost it as we got into town behind buildings.  we ended up driving around the town for a few minutes.  then i decided we had to see if it was still there, so we drove to the west side of the small town and by that time we could no longer see it. 

on the drive, i took an iphone picture that clearly shows the rectangular, white or reflective shape that we saw.  i eventually took at a better camera and took another picture and a small video.  this camera picture and video don't show up as white.  i assume it has something to do with the type of lens, white balance, etc.  it's a better camera, but the images aren't as defined.  this picture and video just show up as a dark spot in the sky. 

our hope in submitting this is that someone knows what this was and can explain it in real terms.  i've never posted anything like this and was hesitant to do so.  but, it was a strange site, and i am hoping someone knows what it was.    

i've included the original iphone picture and a blowup of that, as well as the picture and video from the other camera.
content.summary: Observed large rectangular object that appeared white or reflective during the day

content.detailedDescription:
I was in my bedroom on the second floor listening to music when i looked out my window to stare off like i usually do when i am bored. i stared awhile when i saw a star that appeared "off" i went outside and lost sight of it. a few hours later i looked back out my window and saw it again moving (seemed low) across the sky followed by a jet.(i tried to get it on my iphone but the camera was unable to see them) the ufo stopped and turned then the jet circled it three times but on the third time it flew away. the object stayed stationary and something confusing happened. as the jet vanished so did the ufo but it left behind a smaller object which stayed hovering. it was still for half an hour at least until it pulsed a blue light and you could see the reflection of said light on the small layer of clouds passing over. it stayed still for a long time more until it ejected a small blue light the flew across the sky like a bullet. 10 or so minutes later a second plane headed toward it. the plane was on a direct path when it suddenly banked and headed off away from it. lost the plane really quick but then the ufo started circling a small part of the sky. it did this until it inevitably vanished at around 3:04. i was mostly in awe watching it and was really disappointed that i did not have a camera to record it.
some interesting things that i should mention:
the fighter was really low and so was the ufo at first. 
i was with my friend who also saw it all. i called her over when i saw it both times.
the small blue light looked artificial and flew faster then anything i have ever seen.
a third plane that looked different then any i ever saw passed by the ufo at one point but seemed unphased so i didn't mention it above.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Fighter jets tailed orangish blue object through sky then circled it and bugged out. ufo lingered awhile after

content.detailedDescription:
1. on lake st. clair in anchor bay heading west. near entrance of selfridge angb heading west to dock boat. about 150 yds. from the shore. setting sun in west. late spring/early fall.(not sure) looking east over canada. high cumulus cloud due east lit by setting sun.
2. bright point of light due east in front of clouds.
3. landing aircraft.
4. grew in size over the course of 5-10 min. rectangular. ratio approx. 5:1. sharp 90 deg. corners. luminescent yellow with a fuzzy/crawley background similar to a tv that has no input. red,green,and blue dashed lines in front of the yellow.(yes, the primary colors) dashed rgb lines ran right to left/ left to right that would also switch place with each other.( a green dashed line would run to the right with a blue run to the left with a red dashed line run right. then they would switch place with each other.) only three lines of rgb. one above the the other.
5. puzzlement.
6. selfridge angb dispatched two f 106 delta dart. they flew in full after burner toward the object. about 2-3 miles out, the f 106's went mach 1, and just as they flew beyond visual range, they went mach 2. this was apparent by the sonic booms they produced. within 30 sec. to 1 min. after the jets second sonic booms, the object seemed to blink out, and was gone.

 on the the boat that day, was my father, stepmother, brother, are guests,(recently retired usaf),lt.Col. boe yodel(f 4 phantom pilot with 3-4 vietnam tours), his wife, and i. my father stopped the boat, so as we could observe the object. 100 ft. or so from us was a macomb county sheriff's boat, with two deputies observing the object, along with hundreds of people on the shore observing also.

 we landed the boat about 5 min. latter at our usall dock, which was located within 200 ft. of the entrance of selfridge angb. the gates were barricaded by the post mp's with displaced rifles.

 i was at an air show at selfridge angb in 1994-5 with a friend of mine. while looking at the parked aircraft we went into a hangar that had an f16 on display that was mounted on three tripods and lowered so as people could see the top side of it, and in attendance was a usaf tech sgt.. my friend and i asked some questions about the f 16, then i asked the tech, sgt. as to how often does selfridge have to dispatch aircraft to investigate ufo's, to which he just smirked. then i started to describe what i had witnessed back in 1970. as i was describing the object, he stopped me and said that he was on the base that day himself with his father who was in the air force at the time, and stationed there, and that he had witnessed the object. 

 years later while living in texas, i drove to roswell n.M.. while there i stopped at the roswell ufo museum and purchased 3-4 copies of "incident" magazine, and in the back of one them, there was 1-2 pages of people's various sightings. one of them describer something very similar to what i had witnessed. 

 i was 12 yr.S old when i saw that thing over the lake. i'm 58 yr.S old now, and still don't know what it is that i saw. it could not be described as anything mechanical. my father was in the luftwaffe during ww2, and inherited his interest in aviation, and grew up during one of the human race's greatest era of space explorations. when i look to sky, i do not see ufo's everywhere, and i know that a bright point light in the sky is venise or if it's moving without blinking, it's a satellite, and discount 99.99% of what i see on the internet. 

 i'm hopping that your organization might help me with my search for an answer.

 thanx.
content.summary: Rectangular. luminescent,yellow. dashed rgb lines.

content.detailedDescription: I was walking through the parking lot at work going to my car for break. the moon was full and there was a large chem trail that was lit up by the moon. i thought it would make a good picture so i took out my cell phone and snapped a shot. the pic came out really dark so i thought nothing more of it. last week i was going through my phone and saw the pic again. i figured i would brighten it up hoping that i would be able to see the pic better. when i brightened it a red object with some sort of glowing orb underneath it showed up. at the time i took the pic i didnt see anything. i cant figure out what it is. but when i go back to the dark pic and zoom in i can see the orb faintly. it appears to have been really large because it seems to be partially behind the chem trail left by a jet. there is an electrical pole in the pic. i thought maybe it might be a light of some sort extended up from the pole, but when i looked again during the day there is nothing there so whatever i picked up in the pic was up in the sky. i've never seen anything like it before. if you have an idea of what it could be please share. i'm very curious about it. i have seen unidentified objects twice before years ago and it didnt look like this. i used an app called picsart to brighten the photo. i thought that maybe the brighten and contrast part of the app may have left something in the pic but it doesnt do that with any other pics i have taken. thank you for your time.
content.summary: Red object with white orb appeared in photograph

content.detailedDescription: It was saturday, january 2nd, 2016, 11:45 am. i was running an errand to a store in crete, illinois. i was alone in my car driving east on steger road(a two lane road), between 25-35 mph with my windows rolled up. i believe the sky was mostly overcast that day. as i was calmly enjoying the drive, looking around at the scenery, i happened to notice what looked like a medium-sized plane flying off in the distance, going in the same direction i was going, paralleling my path on steger road. i watched it for a few seconds, then curiously asked myself, "what kind of plane is that?" as i kept watching it, it suddenly began accelerating ahead of me. that's when i said to myself, "that's no airplane; that's a ufo." i knew that planes don't suddenly accelerate like that. at that moment i rolled my window down and took my cellphone off my waist to try to take a photo of it. but by the time i unlocked my screen and turned on the camera, (which took me about 5 seconds)a thick row of trees were blocking my view of it. there were no cars in front of me, so i quickly sped up because i knew there was a huge opening beyond the trees with no homes or buildings to obstruct my view. it would allow me to see the craft and hopefully get a photograph of it. it took me about 6 seconds to reach the opening. but to my shock and surprise the craft was completely gone; nowhere to be seen. the open field was near my destination so i pulled into the parking lot, got out of my car with cell camera in hand and stood there for about a thirty seconds staring across the sky in disbelief while at the same time hoping that the craft would reappear so i could catch a snapshot. but unfortunately, it was not to be.
content.summary: Spotted ufo flying while driving car

content.detailedDescription: I was driving down a back road in knoxville, tn on january 7 around 1:30am with two other friends. we where on our way to their house. we where just talking, then we all noticed out the front window a ball or orb light in the sky. it was several miles away, and i first i thought it could have been a falling star, but then i noticed that it was green. it came straight down a vertical line in the sky, i was just amazed at first, i think i even stopped the car there in the middle of the road. it didn't last too long just a few seconds and it disappeared in the middle of the sky. we started freaking out. i felt my stomach drop and my heart started racing, i thought i was going to be sick. then just a few seconds later a street light blew out, then later another one blew out. i dropped my friends off at work and went home and told my mammow what had happened and what we saw. she goes and to tell me that around the sametime she was laying in her bed on her kendle when she saw a flash of light come from her window and she said it sounded like metal, she thought maybe i had come home and it was just my car so she went to the window but i wasn't there.
content.summary: Saw a ball/ orb of green light come straight down in the sky

content.detailedDescription:
6:10pm, five star display coming in from the east, going west. this is earlier than it was last summer. it has been coming in since 1993, the only change it makes is the time in which it comes in. 6:50pm, it's in close, i took two 35mm photos using an olympus 35mm camera with a shutter speed of 1/60th a second, using 400 speed film. tonight the skies are clear with multiple craft flying in various directions. the five star can only be seen on clear nights. a small white blinking craft flying parallel to hwy. 174, flying south to north. a second white blinking craft flying north to south, parallel to hwy. 174, beneath the five star display. the second should appear in the two photos i took. no sound from any objects. 7:30pm, five star display has stopped coming west, it has stopped short of hwy. 174, which runs directly in front of my home. same pattern since 1993. at this point two other craft appear coming in behind the five star display. both are flashing red, blue, green, and white. they are far apart, directly in line with one another. coming in from the east, going west and lower than the five star display. since 1993, i've witnessed these two having the ability to travel from one horizon to the other in less than five seconds. they can also vanish and re-appear else where in the sky. after those two, there will be two others coming in from same direction, same pattern, the four make up a square shape in the sky, behind and lower than the five star. as the four get closer, they get higher in the sky. 
8:00pm the five star is now going up into outer space, i know this cause the objects are getting smaller as it goes up. the four behind go up as well. these objects defy the earth's rotation. there's an underground lockheed micro-wave base about two miles from my home, going toward walnut springs. i believe these objects has something to do with that base. i believe the five star display is some kind of space station. i have named the four behind as guardians, for i believe they are protecting the five star and are armed with a laser weapon. last month this display was coming in around 9:00pm and last summer it was coming in around 3:00am. it always stops short of hwy. 174, slowly climbing higher, as morning comes it disappears. at 8:00pm i took one more photo on a roll of 24. since it's been cloudy, soon as it clears it all will be visible again. when the roll is finished, i'll have it developed and get it to your director larry weeden of harker heights chapter / section 9. every night here in morgan, the sky is full of ufo's. everyone here ignores them, not caring to find out what they are and morgan is a small unknown town, so no one pays any attention to what goes on. that's why there's so much activity here, they go un-noticed.

content.detailedDescription:
Since these events happened in the same area and within a relatively short time,i am reporting them together as follows:



first, i noticed what looked to be a fireball. a flickering yellow light, not dropping, but moving at a steady rate from west to east. speed direction and apparent altitude did not change for the ten minutes i had it in sight.
(not long ago i was informed there has been "a rash of chinese lantern reports" in recent weeks, so that may explain this one. not 100% sure, but, a possibility.)

there was a celestial yo-yo. a steady, bright, yellow light moving from north to south. every few seconds a smaller light, red or white, would shoot off, go a short distance ahead, then snap back. lost this one behind a tree line after about three minutes.

finally, i found a wandering star. i noticed a bright, stationary, orange light to the southwest. after watching the commercial traffic for several minutes, this light began to move slowly to the east. when it got to my due south, the speed quickly increased. the light made two direction changes but continued moving east. this one, too, i lost behind trees.

content.detailedDescription:
At 1740 local time, i was headed west on allen's lane in evansville, indiana.  upon passing the railroad tracks, i noticed what appeared to be a basketball-sized purple orb move from right to left in front of me to my 2 o'clock position.

orb appeared, at that point, to be just above the top of the trees that surrounded the small, grass-strip airport there.  the  color was a dark purple and the orb, from that distance, looked like a plasma ball.  when it moved, it moved very smoothly and consistently.  it did not seem to bounce around.

as i got closer, the orb started moving west, away from me, and went over the trees to the east of the airport.  i pulled into a parking lot on the north side of allen's lane and was able to catch a short video as it disappeared.  i was facing north in the parking lot and looking west.  orb disappeared at my 8-9 direction.

i sat there for a minute or so and, just as i decided to leave, the orb appeared again, this time at my 11-12 position, just above the trees and appeared to be much farther away, possibly as far as st. joseph avenue and mill road intersection.  according to the distance measuring tool on google maps, that would have put it approximately 1.3 miles away.  this time, i took a second, 7-minute video of the orb rising, lowering and moving around until it disappeared.

when it disappeared for the 2nd time, i waited about 10 minutes and then left the area.

fast forward 2 hours.  i went to pick up my wife and took her to dinner.  i told her about the encounter and, when we were returning, we came over mesker park hill (just south of west diamond avenue on st. joseph avenue) and there it was again, directly north of us.  we were about 1/3rd down the hill when we saw it and it was well above the height we were.

this time, however, the orb looked different.  in addition to the spherical plasma ball, it appeared to have two plasma ellipses, one at the 10 o'clock position and one at the 2 o'clock position centered on the orb.

we had to stop at the stoplight crossing diamond avenue and it appeared that the person in the truck in front of us saw it, as well.

we pulled into the rural king at 2800 n st joseph ave, evansville, in 47720 and parked in the north eastern corner of the parking lot where we took another video that lasted 1 minute and 42 seconds long as the orb appeared to remain at it's height, but traveled north above or paralleling st. joseph avenue until it went out of sight.

at no time, during either encounter, did i hear any noise coming from the orb.  during the first sighting, i was parked in a very quiet area.  i did not get the feeling that this was a drone as it did not seem to wobble or waver.  it moved excruciatingly smoothly and very fast, at times.  i'm not one who is up on modern private drone technology, but the object i saw avoided the trees, powerlines and buildings and travelled anywhere from 1-3 miles requiring a line of sight for control to be from 1/2 a mile to 1-1/2 miles.  but even then, the controller would not have been able to see the drone when it was behind the trees or buildings around the area where i first saw the orb.

please note, i do have three videos on my cell phone, but all are larger than 20 megs (the 7-minute video is over 800m).  i get an error message when i tried to email the videos to myself that i cannot attach anything larger than 20m.  if i can get directions on how to overcome this (no, my  phone doesn't have a removable memory card), i'd be more than glad to share them.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Two separate sightings of purple orb within 2 hours at same general  location, have video..

content.detailedDescription: My son and i were watching the fish in the aquarium i had just set up recently in our home. we were sitting in front of it, and to the right of us are sliding glass doors. it was around 8:45 at night and i happened to look out the window and saw what i thought was a small airplane about to fly over our house. i then said "look, there's an airplane about to fly over our house!" i put my son in the seat and opened the door to get a better look at it. it was very quiet, and was moving very slowly.. i instantly realized that it was not an airplane and called my husband over to see it. i said, "i think it's a drone?? but it's too big to be a drone, and it's a diamond shape, that's so weird!" it had four white lights. two bright wing lights, a nose light, and i think a smaller light in the back. i feel like it was the size of a couple of cars, or the size of a small aircraft that seats two people. my husband began to think that one of our neighbors must own a drone, but i said- there's no way someone could buy a drone that large for personal use and fly it. it looks like someone could ride in it. i bet it's a government drone. i called two air force bases, and they both said they did not have any unmanned drones like the one i described. i did research to try and find drones in the shape and size like the one i saw, but only found this one that really seems to match the description of what i saw: the us navys x-47b drone. i called two local air force bases and they denied having any drones. there was a slightly rounded curved  bottom that i could only see via the shadows that were made from the nose and wing lights that would correspond with the x47b drone, but it's just really bizarre, the whole thing. none of my neighbors saw it, only my husband and myself. how frustrating that i did't get any videos or photos of it, it was so close!!!

content.detailedDescription: My husband and i went outside on our back deck. he flashed the camera once in the direction over the house and i was looking in the opposite direction over the trees and i saw "it" flash back. he flashed the camera again in the same direction over the house and he also saw a flash back and then it dimmed and started moving and then disappeared. same kind of light we've seen in the past. no known visible satellites or flares in area at that time.
content.summary: Flashed back when we flashed a camera

content.detailedDescription: It was roughly 1998 give or take a year not exactly sure  the night before halloween, i was a young boy out doing typical things that boys do this time of year called corning with a few friends. as the night went on we soon got bored and needed a little more excitement. i had a m100 firework, which is a very small explosive device. one of my friends came up with the bright idea to throw it in another kids mailbox as a prank. we didn't really realize what we were getting ourselves into. so my friend lights and then throws the firework into the mailbox and we take off running toward the playground crossing a creek on the way. as we were running we heard what was a very very loud boom. we kept running, then about 1 minute after the explosion as we crossed the playground something stopped us in our tracks. as we turned around to see where a sudden light source that came out of nowhere was there was something hovering about 20 ft over the same basketball court we just seconds earlier ran across. we sat there staring with our mouths wide open, nobody said a word. then all the sudden after it hovered for a few minutes it was just gone. there was no noise and no air coming from the object. the light was way too bright to see the size or shape of the object. i always thought it had to be a government technology that the public doesn't know about because it was there because of the explosion that took place right before the sighting. the funny thing is that none of us there that night ever told anyone nor did we even say anything to each other about the event. this happened in bovard, pennsylvania.
content.summary: Brightest light ever seen about 35 ft away from me hovering silently 20 ft from ground air was still

content.detailedDescription: I was checking christmas lights and taking pictures at a clients home, i had left my camera open and snapped a series of photos unknowingly as i walked the property. i noticed this pic when i got home as i reviewed the house photos i had taken. i remember 2 things very clearly. i sat my phone on the ground and i heard a humming sound in my ears, i want to say it messed a bit with my vision but i'm not sure, i do know i felt my belly felt uneasy,but than again it was late and i hadn't eaten at this point..
content.summary: I can't describe this ,you have to look at the pic i have no clue
